## 5. Proof-effort map (where the real work is)

| Piece | Content | Difficulty | Mathlib levers |
|---|---|---|---|
| `replicatorSel` well-defined | `sum_one`, `nonneg`; `Z>0` on floor | low | `Finset.sum`, `Real.exp_pos` |
| `uMin`, `δ = μ·u_min` bounds | floor ⇒ `w_r ≥ δ`, `Z ≥ δe^{−B}` | low | `Finset.min'`, `Finset.single_le_sum` |
| `g_r = exp f_r` Lipschitz on region | `|e^a − e^b| ≤ e^{B}|a−b|` | low–med | `Real.add_pow_le_pow_mul_pow_of_sq_le`? no — `Real.exp` MVT: `Real.abs_exp_sub_…` / `Convex` |
| `1/Z` Lipschitz on region | `|1/Z − 1/Z'| ≤ |Z−Z'|/(inf Z)^2` | med | `inf Z ≥ δe^{−B}`; quotient bound by hand |
| **product/quotient assembly → `L_R μ`** | finite product rule, sup metric | **med–high** | `dist_pi_le_iff`, triangle, the §3 constant bookkeeping |
| `replicator_contracts_on_band` | `(1−μ)C < (μ u_min)^2` root analysis | med | `Polynomial`/`nlinarith`; monotonicity, one crossing |
| assembly update | `deferred → partial_band/discharged` | low | — |

The single genuinely new proof, exactly as `02-design` predicted, is the
product/quotient Lipschitz assembly (`replicatorLipschitz.bound`) in the **sup**
metric. Everything else is bookkeeping or already-proved plumbing. There is no
`sorry` anywhere in the target; the fitness data `(B, L_f)` enters as explicit
hypotheses (the linear payoff `f = A·w` discharges them with `B = L_f = ‖A‖_∞`), so
nothing is smuggled as an axiom.

